@authBaseUrl = http://localhost:8081
@userBaseUrl = http://localhost:8082

### Auth Service Tests

### 1. Test Controller (Auth Service Status)
# Check if Auth Service is running properly.
GET {{authBaseUrl}}/test

###

### 2. User Signup (Auth Service)
# Register a new user.
POST {{authBaseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@fincz.com",
    "password": "java@123"
}

###

### 3. User Login (Auth Service)
# @name login
# Authenticate and store the returned JWT in a global variable.
POST {{authBaseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@fincz.com",
    "password": "java@123"
}

###

@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 3.1 Create User Profile (User Service)
# Create user profile in user-service after signup
POST {{userBaseUrl}}/users/profile
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@fincz.com",
    "password": "dummy_password"
}

###

### User Service Tests

### 4. Get Current User (User Service)
# Use the JWT from the login request to call the protected user endpoint.
GET {{userBaseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Update Current User (User Service)
# Update the authenticated user's profile.
PUT {{userBaseUrl}}/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "name": "Updated User",
    "phone": "+12345678901",
    "age": 30,
    "occupation": "Engineer",
    "financialGoals": "Save for retirement"
}

###

### 6. Get User by ID (User Service)
# Fetch a user by its numeric ID.
GET {{userBaseUrl}}/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}